--to create a element in react js
--react.createElement()
Syntax:
Type=tag name(h1,p,div)
Prop=class,id
ReactDOM.createRoot() -- to render the element
React element =what to render
Container=where to render
JSX:
Javascript xml
--It is a syntax extension for javascript.
--Jsx allows us to write html code in react js
--Jsx all tags must be closed
--Jsx compiles html code into js
--Babel is a tool in jsx
Funtions:
Using a function call;
--you can use a function call directly in the jsx expression.
